      "content": "hey so i need to ask u something. i've been noticing this thing lately where when i talk to people i can literally feel a vibration in my chest if they aren't being honest. like it's almost like a frequency or a pitch shift in their voice that sounds \"off\" or dissonant. i tried it on my coworker today and it was so obvious it actually made me feel kind of sick. is there any actual way to explain why my body would react to someone lying like that?",
